One final presentation tip

There is one sentence that I think should become the theme of your entire presentation. I'd even put it on one of the early slides in large font:

"Our objective is not to replace analysts. It is to eliminate the manual cognitive work surrounding resilience decisions."

Everything you've described over the last several days—BIA comparisons, BCP reviews, governance intake, crisis planning, bridge call support—fits under that single statement.

When people ask, "What does AI actually do?", you can always come back to that answer. It's business-focused, realistic, and aligns with how successful enterprise AI is being adopted today. I think it will resonate strongly with both your manager and the wider audience.
